  "title": "Programme Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>OnePeople.sg </strong>(OPSG) was launched in May 2007 to champion racial harmony and social cohesion in Singapore. OPSG works hand in hand with community partners, organisations and individuals to promote programmes and initiatives that foster deeper interaction, understanding and appreciation of our multi-ethnic and multi-religious community. </p><p>We are seeking dynamic individuals with a high level of initiative to join our team as: </p><p><strong>PROGRAMME MANAGER </strong></p><p>You will initiate and develop initiatives on youth outreach and engagement, and community engagement. You will also spearhead engagement and development of volunteers/facilitators, build community partnerships and lead initiatives promoting workplace diversity.</p><p><strong>Key requirements:</strong></p><p>*  Degree with at least a year of relevant working experience. </p><p>*  Passion for inter-racial/inter-religious community work</p><p>*  Proven ability in conceptualising and developing outreach and capacity building programmes for youths, volunteers, community leaders, workplaces and/or educators in areas of intercultural/interfaith understanding, advocacy and cross-cultural engagement</p><p>*  Track record in volunteer management, partnership development and/or corporate engagement</p><p>*  Curating facilitated conversations on cross cultural relations and social cohesion </p><p>*  Experience preferably in:</p><p>-  Programme/event management, administration, evaluation and social media engagement</p><p>-  Track record in working with youth-based organisations, schools, grassroots/community organisations, volunteers and/or corporates</p><p>*  Adaptable, strong interpersonal skills, analytical and objective-driven </p><p>*  Ability to work well in teams yet competent in managing projects independently</p><p>If you are a highly motivated individual who has what it takes, we welcome you to join us. Salary will be commensurate with working experience and qualifications. </p><p>Closing date of application: 20 February 2026</p><p>Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>",
